<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1599> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1599" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The death of Veturius forced Licinius to abdicate before they had completed any of their regular duties (Liv. 27.6.17-18, and 34.5-6; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 46f., 120, 448f.). On Veturius, see Lübker, no. 8." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1330> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1330" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Appointed to hold elections but abdicated vitio creatus (Fast. Cap., Degrassi 44f., 118, 444f.; Liv. 22.33.11-12). See Lübker, no. 8." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1280> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1280" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Hyd. (Catulo et Filone); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod. (L. Veturius et C. Lutatius); Zon. 8.20; and on Lutatius, Polyb. 3.40.9. See Degrassi 118, 442f. The Consuls together led an expedition as far as the Alps (Zon. 8.20). On Veturius, see Lübker no. 8." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1279> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1279" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Catulus was probably a son of the Consul of 242. Philo's filiation is given in Fast. Cap. on the Dictator of 217 and the Censor of 210." .
